<br>
Wizard #1 is chain casting Shock of Lightning, lvl 12, with 2 foot knockback.  Even if resisted, the knockback interrupts your spells every time.<br>
<br>
Wizard #2 is chain casting Ice Comet, took 3 casts to kill me because of my resists.<br>
<br>
Pet's DD disrupted the IC wiz once, but he was able to cast on me to kill me.  I tried to chain-cast Gate, but the knockback interrupted me 5 (!) times (I was not SoW'ed, and was too far to run)<br>
<br>
I need suggestions on how to counter this.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udinthor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dinthor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(8/27/01 2:25:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beatdown by a pair of Wizards</span><hr size=1> You are screwed.. you can't win in that situation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umezlothemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mezlo the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#333333>(8/27/01 5:23:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beatdown by a pair of Wizards</span><hr size=1> 2 on one is always bad.  Getting caught surprised or unprepared is bad.<br>
<br>
You basicly had four choices: gate, run, try to kill the lower wizard, dispell the pet.<br>
<br>
You tried to gate, nothing wrong with this choice.<br>
<br>
Running might have worked unless you got rooted, the range on a bolt is phenominal but the wizard has to stop to cast and you can just keep running.  You might have made it, with a little luck.<br>
<br>
Assuming the wizard casting shock of lightening was lower, you might be able to turn on him and kill him out right with faster lower level spells.<br>
<br>
And finally, you might have been able to dispell the pet and get him on one of the wizards, keep it dispelled and one of the wizards is going to die.<br>
<br>
It was a bad situation and you where not going to win.  Remember dispel the pet, and run from casters.  They have to stand still to cast and you can get distance.  Better luck next time.<br>
<br>
