<br>
If you're getting hit with Shock of Lightning, note that it's not a &quot;true&quot; interrupt.  It only interrupts because it moves you.<br>
<br>
After getting zapped, step back up and you stand a good chance of channeling your spell.  As long as your spell completes casting in the same LOC where you started it, you can channel it.  You can run figure 8's and still complete a spell as long as you stop exactly where you started.<br>
<br>
